{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox newspaper | name = Lausitzer Rundschau | logo = Lausitzer Rundschau logo.svg | image = | caption = | type = [[Daily newspaper]] | format = [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|Tabloid]] | owners = [[Georg von Holtzbrinck Publishing Group]] | founder = | publisher = LR Medienverlag und Druckerei GmbH | editor = | chiefeditor = | foundation = {{start date and age|df=y|1946|5|20}} | political = | language = [[German language|German]] | headquarters = [[Cottbus]], Germany | circulation = | ISSN = | oclc = | website = {{official website|http://www.lr-online.de/}} }}
'''''Lausitzer Rundschau''''' is a German language daily regional newspaper published in [[Cottbus]], [[Brandenburg (city)|Brandenburg]], [[Germany]].
==History and profile== ''Lausitzer Rundschau'' was first published on 20 May 1946.<ref name=geslr>{{cite web|title=Geschichte|url=http://www.lr-online.de/unternehmen/ueberuns/art205521,3704983|work=Lausitzer Rundschau|accessdate=20 April 2015}}</ref> In 1952 the offices of the paper moved to [[Görlitz]] and the paper consisted of eight pages.<ref name=geslr/> On 5 August 1952 the paper moved to its current headquarters in Cottbus.<ref name=geslr/><ref>{{cite web|title=Tabloid Format Used to Counter Falling Circulation|url=http://www.mullermartini.com/us/desktopdefault.aspx/tabid-229/669_read-1833/|work=Muller Martini USA|accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref>
The paper was owned by the [[Socialist Unity Party of Germany|Socialist Unity Party]] before [[German reunification]].<ref name=nyu>{{cite news|title=United Germany Today: Clearly Western, Still Divided, or Still Searching?|url=http://www.nyu.edu/deutscheshaus/email/ERP.pdf|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=New York University|date=5 November 2009}}</ref><ref name=boy>{{cite book|author=Dominic Boyer|title=Spirit and System: Media, Intellectuals, and the Dialectic in Modern German Culture|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=j67InfxRfLsC&pg=PA148|accessdate=14 March 2015|date=1 December 2005|publisher=University of Chicago Press|isbn=978-0-226-06891-6|page=148}}</ref> Following the unification the owner of the daily became [[Georg von Holtzbrinck Publishing Group]].<ref name=nyu/><ref>{{cite journal|author1=Andrea Czepek|author2=Ulrike Klinger|title=Media Pluralism Between Market Mechanisms and Control: The German Divide|journal=International Journal of Communication|date=2010|volume=4|url=http://storage.globalcitizen.net/data/topic/knowledge/uploads/20130619151546656208_Media%20Pluralism%20Between%20Market%20Mechanisms%20and%20Control%20-%20The%20German%20Divide.pdf|accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=cci>{{cite web|title=Lausitzer Rundschau to join Saarbrücker Zeitung´s CCI editorial system|url=http://www.ccieurope.com/Default.aspx?ID=1034&PID=5815&M=NewsV2&Action=1&NewsId=82|work=CCI Europe|accessdate=14 March 2015|format=Press Release|date=7 November 2008}}</ref> The company also owns other newspapers, including ''[[Saarbrücker Zeitung]]''.<ref name=dward/><ref>{{cite book|author1=Anthony Weymouth|author2=Bernard Lamizet|title=Markets and Myths: Forces For Change In the European Media|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OMO3AwAAQBAJ&pg=PT206|accessdate=12 April 2015|date=3 June 2014|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-1-317-88969-4|page=206}}</ref>
''Lausitzer Rundschau'' is published in [[tabloid format]] by a subsidiary of the Saarbrücker Zeitung Group,<ref name=xin/><ref>{{cite web|title=Rheinische Post Media Group|url=http://www.euroscript.com/cs/Satellite/ESC/PressRelease/1359990671370/1349859361418/en_UK/Press_Release_%7C_Rheinische_Post_Media_Group.html|work=euroscript|accessdate=14 March 2015|format=Press Release|date=12 September 2012}}</ref> LR Medienverlag und Druckerei GmbH.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lausitzer Rundschau|url=http://www.drehscheibe.org/tl_files/drehscheibe/Ideen/Deutschlandkarte_2013_neu/Lausitzer_Rundschau_2013_neu.pdf|work=Zeitungslandschaft|accessdate=20 April 2015}}</ref> In September 2012 the majority share of Saarbrücker Zeitung Group was acquired by Rheinische Post Mediengruppe.<ref name=rpm>{{cite news|title=Rheinische Post Mediengruppe acquires majority shareholding in the Saarbrücker Zeitungsgruppe|url=http://www.rheinischepostmediengruppe.de/eng/Press/Rheinische-Post-Mediengruppe-acquires-majority-shareholding-in-the-Saarbruecker-Zeitungsgruppe|accessdate=20 April 2015|work=Rheinische Post Mediengruppe|date=September 2012}}</ref>
The paper serves the states of [[Brandenburg]] and [[Saxony]],<ref name=xin/> and has 13 editions.<ref name=cci/><ref>{{cite web|title=Lausitzer Rundschau|url=http://www.rheinischepostmediengruppe.de/eng/Business-segments/Daily-newspapers/Saarbruecker-Zeitungsgruppe|work=Rheinische Post Medien Gruppe|accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref> Since 2 March 2006 ''LR-Woche'', a free weekly tabloid, has been delivered with the paper.<ref>{{cite journal|title=The march of the non-dailies|journal=FDN Newsletter|date=March 2006|issue=15|url=http://www.newspaperinnovation.com/newsletters/newsletter1506.pdf|accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref>
''Lausitzer Rundschau'' was called Lügenrudi (meaning Liar Tom in English) when it was published in [[East Germany]].<ref name=boy/> The daily publishes extensive reports on [[Neo-Nazism|neo-nazi]] activity in the region.<ref name=xin/> The offices of ''Lausitzer Rundschau'' has been target for the attacks by [[Right-wing extremism|right-wing extremists]] in [[Lübbenau]] and [[Spremberg]].<ref name=xin>{{cite news|author=Catherine Stupp|title=Vandals lash out against local newspaper for reporting on right-wing extremists|url=http://www.indexoncensorship.org/2014/09/eastern-germany-vandals-lashed-local-newspapers-reporting-right-wing-extremists/|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=XIndex|date=15 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Neo-Nazis Suspected in Torching of Journalist's Car|url=http://en.rsf.org/germany-neo-nazis-suspected-in-torching-of-30-12-2014,47433.html|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=Reporters without Borders|date=30 December 2014}}</ref>
The circulation of ''Lausitzer Rundschau'' was 100,000 copies in January 1954.<ref name=geslr/> In the second quarter of 2003 the paper had a circulation of 136,259 copies.<ref name=dward>{{cite web|author=David Ward|title=A mapping study of media concentration and ownership in ten European countries|url=http://77.87.161.246/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/A-Mapping-Study-of-Media-Concentration-and-Ownership-in-Ten-European-Countries.pdf|work=Commissariaat voor de Media|accessdate=14 March 2015|location=Hilversum|date=2004}}</ref>
