{{COI|date=May 2009}} '''Michael Pärt Musik''' is an Icelandic-Estonian film music, sound and music production company founded by music producer [[Michael Pärt]]. The company is focused on score and soundtrack productions for feature films, TV and documentaries. In addition to producing, Michael Pärt Musik deals with engineering, editing, mixing and a little composing as well. Some of the highlights of the company include collaborations with film director [[Francis Ford Coppola]], composers [[Howard Shore]], [[Richard Harvey]], [[Osvaldo Golijov]], rock band [[Arcade Fire]] and Icelandic pop artist [[Björk]].
==Current activities==
===International Arvo Pärt Centre=== In 2008 he returned to Estonia, the homeland of his father and the country where he was born to establish <ref>[http://www.postimees.ee/?id=176392 Michael Pärt Establishes the "Arvo Pärt Archive"]</ref> the [[International Arvo Pärt Centre]] <ref>[http://www.arvopart.ee/en International Arvo Pärt Centre]</ref> which he chairs. The foundation preserves [[Arvo Pärt]]'s creative contribution to the arts and ensures education for future generations.
