{{Infobox video game | title = The Missing: J.J. Macfield and the Island of Memories | image = The Missing J.J. Macfield and the Island of Memories.jpg | alt = | caption = | developer = White Owls Inc. | publisher = [[Arc System Works]] | director = | producer = | designer = | programmer = | artist = | writer = | composer = | series = | engine = | platforms = [[Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox One]], [[Nintendo Switch]] | released = 12 October 2018 | genre = [[Puzzle-platformer]] | modes = [[Single-player]] }} '''''The Missing: J.J. Macfield and the Island of Memories''''' is a [[puzzle-platformer]] horror video game developed by [[Hidetaka Suehiro]]'s White Owls Inc. for [[Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox One]], and [[Nintendo Switch]]. It was published by [[Arc System Works]] and released on 12 October 2018.
==Overview== The game's premise is that J.J. Macfield, the player character, is searching for her friend and love interest Emily after she goes missing on a camping trip. After J.J. is struck by lightning, she cannot die and must inflict grisly wounds on herself in order to solve the game's puzzles. Throughout, players unlock text messages that reveal her backstory and her motivation for her [[self-harm]].<ref name="Kotaku 16 October 2018">{{cite web |last=Alexandra |first=Heather |title=The Missing Gets Queer Love Stories Right |url=https://kotaku.com/the-missing-gets-queer-love-stories-right-1829784922 |work=[[Kotaku]] |date=16 October 2018 |accessdate=16 October 2018}}</ref>
==Reception== ''[[Kotaku]]'' highlighted the game for being "transgressive and shockingly frank in talking about [[LGTBQA+]] issues".<ref name="Kotaku 16 October 2018" /> ''[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]'' appreciated the game's "surreal mix of coming of age drama and genuinely creepy survival horror", but noted tonal missteps and deficiencies in voice acting and writing.<ref>{{cite news |title=Game review: The Missing: J.J. Macfield And The Island Of Memories is very odd |url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/10/15/the-missing-j-j-macfield-and-the-island-of-memories-review-finding-swery-8041102/ |newspaper=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |date=15 October 2018 |accessdate=16 October 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181015214433/https://metro.co.uk/2018/10/15/the-missing-j-j-macfield-and-the-island-of-memories-review-finding-swery-8041102/ |archivedate=15 October 2018 |deadurl=no}}</ref> ''[[Destructoid]]'', like ''Metro'', considered SWERY to borrow perhaps too heavily from ''[[Twin Peaks]]'', but found ''The Missing'' appealing as a "brave, subtle, and at times cruel ... adventure featuring gorgeous animation, affecting visuals, and stomach-churning sound effects".<ref>{{cite web |last=Moyse |first=Chris |title=Review: The Missing: J.J. Macfield and the Island of Memories |url=https://www.destructoid.com/review-the-missing-j-j-macfield-and-the-island-of-memories-525686.phtml |work=[[Destructoid]] |date=14 October 2018 |accessdate=16 October 2018}}</ref>
The game was nominated for "Games for Impact" at [[The Game Awards 2018]].<ref>{{cite web |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |title=The Game Awards 2018 nominees led by God of War, Red Dead Redemption 2 |url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/11/13/18092186/game-awards-2018-nominees-show-date-start-time |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |date=13 November 2018 |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref>
